In Equation (9), L is the effective length. For instance, applying force at the trailing edge sets L equal to the local chord length at that point. Analysis shows that membrane deformation transfers to the carbon ribs and spars. Hence, the endpoint of the outer wing section’s trailing-edge second rib (refer to Figure 12) is selected as the stiffness measurement point. The stiffness calculated here defines the flapping wing’s chordwise stiffness.
